      • lookup

        public java.util.List<AkkIMEEntry> lookup(java.util.List<AkkUnit> input,
                                          boolean anticipate)
        Description copied from interface: AkkIMEDict
        Find all the words in the dictionary whose Pinyin matches the given input. For input units with no specified tone, the tone should be considered a wildcard and matches for all tones should be returned. Returned entries will have at least as many characters as units in the specified input. If anticipating, then longer words whose first characters match the input can additionally be returned. Returned entries should be in order relative to their frequency, with the most frequent words at the head of the List.
        Specified by:
        lookup in interface AkkIMEDict
        Parameters:
        input - the units of pinyin input
        anticipate - true if words that begin with the input should also be returned
        Returns:
        words matched by the input
